main event: Radar operators at Itazuke AFB, Japan, observed an unidentified object on radar on December 12, 1952.
interesting points: Five radar plots were observed, showing an average speed of 710 knots,The object's course varied from 270° to 240°,The observation lasted for 9 minutes,Five other aircraft were identified in the area at that time,The radar equipment functioned normally during the observation.
